# [PEARG](../wg/pearg.html)

## Summary

The Privacy Enhancing Technologies Research Group (PEARG) met to discuss critical emerging privacy threats and structural issues in the current internet landscape. The session featured two main presentations: an in-depth analysis of the privacy and national security risks associated with Real-Time Bidding (RTB) in online advertising, and a study demonstrating how Large Language Models (LLMs) can be used for automated, low-cost deanonymization at scale. Additionally, the group received an administrative update on a proposed ciphertext inference tool draft and a lightning presentation on source privacy challenges following Encrypted Client Hello (ECH) deployment.

